    <text id="B1250T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Chalfin reports that Jackson's request for a messenger is denied.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Head Quarters First Military District<lb/>State of Virginia
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Lieutenant Colonel">Bvt Lt Col</abbr>
                        W. S. Franklin <abbr expan="United States Army">U.S.A.</abbr><lb/>Commanding
                        Sub District of Winchester<lb/>Winchester <abbr expan="Virginia">V<hi
                                rend="super">a</hi></abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-11-26">November 26th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">V<hi rend="super"
                            >a</hi></abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Referring to your endorsement of the 5th instant, forwarding letter of Mr. <hi
                        rend="underline">Thomas P. Jackson</hi>, Freedmen's Bureau agent, at
                    Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>, who requests the detail of an
                    enlisted man as Messenger in his office. I am directed by the Commanding General
                    to say that the request of Mr. <hi rend="underline">Jackson</hi> is not granted.
                    You will please so inform Mr. <hi rend="underline">Jackson</hi>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your Obedient Servant</salute>
                    <signed>S. F. Chalfin<lb/>Assistant Adjutant General</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Official copy furnished for the information of Mr.
                        Jackson <orig reg="through">thro.</orig>
                        <abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> J.A. McDonnell <abbr
                            expan="Military Commissioner">Mil Comr</abbr> &amp;c Winchester,
                            <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr><lb/>[signed]Walter S.
                            Franklin<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> 21st <abbr
                            expan="Infantry">Inf.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Brevet Lieutenant Colonel, United States Army">Bvt. Lt. Col.
                            USA</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Commanding">Comd<hi rend="super"
                        >g</hi></abbr> Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
